Clean translation of your idea

“mode selection influence = epigenetics for behavior”

That’s actually a strong analogy if you keep the mapping precise.

Biology side (epigenetics)
	•	DNA = full capability space
	•	Epigenetic signals = which genes are expressed
	•	Environment = triggers expression patterns
	•	Outcome = phenotype (what shows up)

OrbitOS / Pantheon side
	•	Actor = capability space (skills, tendencies, history)
	•	Constraint Profile (Mode) = what gets expressed
	•	Context / interaction = triggers
	•	Output = behavior / trajectory

⸻

The mechanism (no magic needed)

Mode Selection Influence = changing which subset of capabilities is active by altering constraints.

That’s it.

Not:
	•	rewriting the person
	•	not controlling them
	•	not “becoming something else”

Just:
	•	shifting expression under constraints

⸻

Why this is powerful (and grounded)

Because most people think:

behavior = personality

But in practice:

behavior = personality × constraints × context

OrbitOS is just:
	•	making that explicit
	•	and trackable over time

