What “modes” really are (repo-ready definition)

Constraint Profile (Mode)

ConstraintProfile {
  name: str
  weights: {
    clarity: float
    rigor: float
    speed: float
    risk_tolerance: float
    empathy: float
    authority: float
    creativity: float
    precision: float
  }
  rules: list[str]
  suppressions: list[str]
}

Examples:
	•	math_teacher
	•	operator
	•	negotiator
	•	explorer
	•	auditor

Each one:
	•	emphasizes some behaviors
	•	suppresses others

⸻

Mode selection as a “force”

In OrbitOS terms:
	•	switching modes = internal perturbation
	•	changing someone else’s mode = external influence attempt
	•	stable modes over time = identity wells
	•	rapid switching = instability or adaptability (context-dependent)

⸻

Where your epigenetics analogy holds

✔ Good:
	•	expression vs capability distinction
	•	environment-driven activation
	•	reversible (mostly)
	•	layered and combinatorial

✖ Where to be careful:
	•	no fixed “genome” for behavior
	•	no precise on/off switches
	•	much noisier and less deterministic
	•	humans can override patterns intentionally

So treat it as:

a guiding analogy, not a literal mapping

